Napoli has resumed training under the watch of manager Gennaro Gattuso, as  Serie A looks to resume soon. Players are split into groups and granted entry to the training ground in staggered times to ensure social distancing. READ ALSO:  Odion Ighalo wants to extend loan Group training is not yet allowed, all the players and staff tested negative for COVID-19 over the last few days, so the doors to the Castel Volturno ground were opened up today. According to reports, Coach Gattuso arrived at the crack of dawn to begin work, as he and his staff have planned out 60-minute sessions for each player. The goalkeepers were the first to arrive, Alex Meret, David Ospina, and Orestis Karnezis each with their own training pitch and a series of sanitized footballs.